==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outskirt
<hw>Out"skirt`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A part remote from
the center, and near the outer edge; border; -- usually in the plural;
<as>as, the <ex>outskirts</ex> of a town</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>outskirts</qex> of his march of mystery.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outsleep</ent>⟦br⟧
